cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with evolutionary algorithms and the tuning of selection pressure. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as evolutionary algorithms are a subfield of AI. The paper also involves comparisons of different selection schemes, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and convergence could also place it in the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
